import os
import re

is_include = re.compile("#include \"(.*)\"")
is_include2 = re.compile("#include\"(.*)\"")


def fix_include(file, paths):
    tmp = "%s.tmp" % file
    ins = open(file)
    ous = open(tmp,'w')
    line = ins.readline()
    found = False
    while line:
        m = is_include.search(line)
        if m and m.group(1) in paths:
            ous.write("#include \"")
            ous.write(paths[m.group(1)])
            ous.write("\"\n")
            found = True
            line = ins.readline()
            continue
        m = is_include2.search(line)
        if m and m.group(1) in paths:
            ous.write("#include \"")
            ous.write(paths[m.group(1)])
            ous.write("\"\n")
            found = True
            line = ins.readline()
            continue
        ous.write(line)            
        line = ins.readline()
    ins.close()
    ous.close()
    if found:
        print(file)
        os.system("move %s %s" % (tmp, file))
    else:
        os.system("del %s" % tmp)
